After a good read of the primary docs (http://docs.jquery.com/Plugins/Validation and http://docs.jquery.com/Plugins/Validation/Reference), I didn't find any clear overview of using the depends parameter in the rules collection.
The big challenge here is knowing that when you use "depends", you need to use "param" to host the parameters. That is unclear and deserves a topic in the docs.

For example:

``` js
$("#TextBox1").rules("add", {
   range: {
      param : [1, 10],
      depends : "#CheckBox1"
   }
}
```

It would help to have a topic on one of these pages focused on dependencies. That topic would discuss the syntax issue related to using "param" as shown.

