There is no `return` statement for the setter, so it returns `undefined`. This gets cached and is returned when `object.get("prop")` is called. What should be returned though is `"value"`.

Obviously this would work, if you always did `return prop;` at the end. But it is easy to forget.  And shouldn't you rather `return this;` for the setter? Because that is what  `set()` returns for regular properties.

